# free-apk-builder â€” Offline-first MVP (Native Android + Docker builder)

This repository is an MVP that:
- Accepts a plain description and generates a simple Native Android (Kotlin) project,
- Builds APKs inside a Dockerized Android builder,
- Stores APK at `storage/apk/{id}.apk`,
- Works offline-first (can call local LLaMA via llama.cpp) and supports online deployment.

Quick start (Linux/macOS)
1. Requirements: Docker, Node.js (v16+), npm
2. After extracting the ZIP:
   cd free-apk-builder
3. Build builder image (once):
   docker build -t android-builder:latest ./builder
4. Start backend:
   cd backend && npm install && npm run dev
5. (Optional) Start frontend:
   cd ../frontend && npm install && npm run dev
6. Generate + build (API):
   curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/generate -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"description":"Simple calculator app with buttons"}'
   Response example: { "id":"1673423456", "apk_url": "http://localhost:8080/download/1673423456" }
7. Download the APK:
   http://localhost:8080/download/{id}

Notes:
- APKs produced are debug-signed for demo and side-loading. For Play Store, use your release keystore and a release-signing pipeline.
- To use local LLaMA: see docs/offline-llama.md
- For production, add sandboxing, rate-limits, auth, and scanning for generated code.
